{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 8.413** (in *Chapter 8*, on judicial proceedings and social duties) states the following rule:\n\n> But he should make a Shudra perform the work of a slave, whether bought or not bought; for he was created by the Self-existent One for the service of a Brahmana.[^1]\n\nThis verse asserts that a Brahmana (\"he\") is entitled to compel any Shudra to perform servile labor—even without purchase—because Shudras were divinely created by Brahma (the Self-existent One) to serve Brahmanas.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, *Chapter 8*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/08/translation/#p-e6bdf4).",
